{{Quote|At Ossus I met Xendor, the man of my vision. He was a Kashi Mer exile, a master of the Breath, as his people called the Force.|Filed selections from the debriefing of [[Arden Lyn]]|<ref name="EGTW">''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]''</ref>}}
[[File:XendorEGW.jpg|thumb|right|250px|[[Xendor]] was an exiled Kashi Mer.]]
The '''Kashi Mer''', also known as the '''Kashi''', was a civilization that inhabited the [[Kashi system]].<ref name="TotJ">''[[Tales of the Jedi Companion]]''</ref>

{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Kashi Mer were first mentioned in the [[Roleplaying game|roleplaying]] adventure "[[Relic (article)|Relic]]," which was authored by [[George R. Strayton]] for use with [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' and published in the [[May]] [[1995]] [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 6|sixth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' magazine.<ref name="Journal6">{{JournalCite|6|Relic (article)}}</ref> Strayton's [[1996]] roleplaying sourcebook ''[[Tales of the Jedi Companion]]'' later introduced the alternate name "Kashi" for the culture.<ref name="TotJC">''[[Tales of the Jedi Companion]]''</ref> The Kashi Mer were first illustrated by [[Conceptopolis]] for the [[2010]] book [[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']].<ref name="JP">[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']]</ref>

